  <h1>
   tan
  </h1>
  In a right angled triangle
  <i>
   tan(val) = Opposite / Adjacent
  </i>
  where val is one of the three angles.
  <b>
   <span>
    NOTE
   </span>
  </b>
  This function takes a value in radians not degrees.
  <b>
   NOTE
  </b>
  : Pi/2, (3 pi/2), -pi/2 and a vast number of other values will error with this function due to their returning infinity, a graph representation of this would produce asymptotes at these values.
  <h4>
   Syntax:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">tan(val);
</code></pre>
  <table>
   <tbody>
    <tr>
     <th>
      Argument
     </th>
     <th>
      Type
     </th>
     <th>
      Description
     </th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      val
     </td>
     <td>
      <span>
       <a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
        Real
       </a>
      </span>
     </td>
     <td>
      The angle (in radians) to return the tangent of.
     </td>
    </tr>
   </tbody>
  </table>
  <h4>
   Returns:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml"><a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
 Real
</a></code></pre>
  <h4>
   Example:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">val = tan( pi );
</code></pre>
  This will set val to 0.
